     <sect1 id="variable.cache.locking">
      <title>$cache_locking</title>
       <para>
        Cache locking avoids concurrent cache generation. This means resource intensive pages can be generated only once, 
        even if they've been requested multiple times in the same moment.
       </para>
       <para>
        Cache locking is disabled by default. To enable it set <varname>$cache_locking</varname> to &true;. 
       </para>
      <para>
       See also
       <link linkend="variable.locking.timeout"><varname>$locking_timeout</varname></link>
      </para>
     </sect1>
